                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> So, in your opinion, one off-handed statement (because that is certainly what it is, considering the context they mentioned it in) on SoE's part regarding the Affliction line being designed for DoTs therefore excludes it from working on everything else and therefore also proves beyond a doubt that they intended it to work ONLY with DoTs?<br /><br />Sorry, but that doesn't sit with me.  There have been hundreds, if not thousands, of threads across every community board calling for SoE to come out with an official statement about whether the Affliction focus items would ever be changed so that they no longer affect things other than DoTs.  SoE, as far as I know, never complied.  <br /><br />Why didn't they? Because it's the policy of SoE to remain vague on issues such as this in case they need to switch gear later on.  Avoid certainties and you can bend policy as you please.  By not coming out and saying whether Affliction focus items should work with root or not, they leave the options open as to whether to nerf or not...  Just as they are doing with the eyes.  Did they ever make an official statement on whether necromancers should be able to tap eyes? No.  <br /><br />Is it too much to ask for one? No, just as it wasn't too much to ask for a explanation of why they chose to nerf Affliction focus items *eight* months after they were first introduced.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Posting unfunded sony bashing in an "Absor doesn't love us" class C rant on the necro board isn't really "contrary to popular opinion". "Jumping the band-wagon" would be more accurate.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Right.  It was all unfounded bashing on SoE.  I see you missed the entire point of my first post and most of my second one, as well.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
